        entry
          definition "One who operates."
        entry
          definition "A telecommunications facilitator whose job is to establish temporary network connections."
        entry
          definition "A function or other mapping that carries variables defined on a domain into another variable or set of variables in a defined range."
        entry
          definition "The game of Chinese whispers."
        entry
          definition "A person who is adept at making deals or getting results, especially one who uses questionable methods."
        entry
          definition "A member of a military special operations unit."
        entry
          definition "The administrator of a channel or network on IRC."
        entry
          definition "A symbol that represents a construct in a programming language and differs from a normal function in its syntax."
        entry
          definition "A kind of expression that enters into an a-bar movement dependency and is said to bind a variable."
          example 'In the sentence "What did Bill say he wants to buy?", "what" is an operator, binding a phonetically empty variable.'
